On 8/2/04 9:42 PM, "Phil Cappellini" <philcappellini(-at-)hotmail.com> wrote:

> My question is how long should it take to remove a tranny and engine. I am
> trying to budget my time? I have removed engines lots of times and it takes
> me about 2 to 3 hours on my own. I have never removed a tranny.

- Undo CV joints
- Remove ground strap
- Unplug backup light switch
- Disconnect clutch cable

Add another 15-30 minutes to your drop time.

